'''Jean-Bernard Sindeu''' is a [[Cameroon]]ian politician who served in the government of Cameroon as Minister of Energy and Water Resources from 2006 to 2009. Considered a technocrat,<ref name=AI>[http://www.africaintelligence.com/C/modules/login/DetailArt/LoginDetailArt.asp?rub=login&lang=ANG&service=ART&context=BOI&doc_i_id=22930163 "Jean Bernard Sindeu"], ''Africa Intelligence'', 4 October 2006.</ref> he was appointed to that position on 22 September 2006.<ref name=AI/><ref>[http://www.postnewsline.com/2006/09/the_rejig_and_s.html "The Rejig And Spanking"], ''The Post'' (Cameroon), 25 September 2006.</ref> He was previously the First Assistant Mayor of [[Bana, Cameroon|Bana]],<ref name=AI/> which is located in [[West Province (Cameroon)|West Province]]; he remains in that position as of 2007.<ref>Elvis Tah, [http://www.postnewsline.com/2007/03/kadji_offers_ne.html "Kadji Offers New Town Hall To Bana Council"], ''The Post'' (Cameroon), 5 March 2007 {{fr icon}}.</ref>

Sindeu was dismissed from the government on 30 June 2009.<ref>Jean-Bruno Tagne, [http://www.cameroon-info.net/cmi_show_news.php?id=25115 "Breaking News: Paul Biya modifie son Gouvernement !"]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, Cameroon-info.net, 30 June 2009 {{fr icon}}.</ref>

