{{Physics stub}}

'''Pressure shale''' is [[shale]] that has been exposed to high pressures that causes it to fracture, usually into large [[wikt:concave|concave]] pieces. In [[mud logging]], watching for this type of shale is one method of monitoring for the possibility of drilling into high pressures that might cause a [[Blowout (well drilling)|blowout]].

